@NODE "Mail_0" " A Pointer (I think) question "
From: Tony Rolfe <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Date: 06-07-00 06:42:13
Subject: @{b}A Pointer (I think) question@{ub}

I currently have the following arrays:

Dim HeadString$(9)
Dim HeadColumn.w(9)
Dim HeadAlign.w(9)

These let me have 9 columns on the screen each containing the string,
aligned according to the align value, at the pixel given in the Column
value.

The problem with this is that I can only have one set of headings
active at any one time.     What I want is to be able to nest
reports such that each can have its own headings.

My plan is to redefine the headings as

NewType .HeadColumn
String.s
Column.w
Align.w
End NewType

Then 
Dim Heading1.HeadColumn(9)
Dim Heading2.HeadColumn(9)
etc.

The problem is...    How do I tell the common routine which set of
headings to process?

I thought of something like *CurrentHeading.l = &Heading1()
but I'm not sure how the common routine would process the columns.

Any thoughts would be appreciated...

Thanks


-- 
