@NODE "Mail_1" " Re: A Pointer (I think) question "
From: David McMinn <D.Mcminn@eee.rgu.ac.uk>
Date: 06-07-00 09:04:11
Subject: @{b}Re: A Pointer (I think) question@{ub}

Hi Tony

> The problem is...    How do I tell the common routine which set of
> headings to process?
> 
> I thought of something like *CurrentHeading.l = &Heading1()
> but I'm not sure how the common routine would process the columns.

It would be easier to use something like:

*CurrentHeading.HeadColumn = &Heading1(0)

Since you know there's always 9 columns in the headings (or you could always 
pass that as another parameter), you could then do something like this in the 
common routine:

Statement doheadings{*CurrentHeading.HeadColumn, win.w}
  For i.w=0 to 8
	; i take it you're using something like TextLength to work out the position

	; Move to position calculated
	Move_ RastPort(win),x,y

	; Draw text onto window
	Text_ RastPort(win),&*CurrentHeading\String

	; Move onto next column heading
	*CurrentHeading = *CurrentHeading + sizeof.HeadColumn
  Next
End Statement

doheadings{&Heading1(0), 0}


