NO!  Gosub returns to wherever you called the routine from, so it can
be accessed from anywhere in your program.

Just like a function, with the exception of the local variables.

It is the equivalent of a machine-language JSR instruction.


GoTo, on the other hand, always goes to one specified place in the code.
 
