@NODE "Mail_85" " Blitz PC update "
From: Mark Sibly <marksibly@blitzbasic.com>
Date: 06-17-00 02:21:51
Subject: @{b}Blitz PC update@{ub}


Yo!

Thanks for everyone's comments.

I'm trying to build up an overall picture of what people want, and this is
what I'm getting:

* Gosub will remain.

* There will be a command line version of Blitz in the Lite release. Many
comments were made about Ted - mousable labels, tokenizing etc - and I don't
wont to get too bogged down in the editor (one of the mistakes I made in
AmiBlitz) so this will allow you to use any editor if you don't like the one
in Blitz.

* There were lots of comments about the library system. Blitz Lite will not
use a library system, so this is all up in the air for now. However, I can
make the following promises about BlitzPro libs: there will be no lib
numbers; you'll be able to write libs in Blitz, ASM, C whatever; there will
be no makedeflibs.

* Regarding MMX/AMD extensions. These are (apparently) built into DirectX,
so there should be no need to mess around with these in Blitz. However, the
inline Blitz assembler MAY support MMX.

I've had lots of requests for the Blitz test. I'll send it out later today
to people who have requested it so far, but that'll probably be it for now.

I'm may be entering a 'quiet' period too...time to get back to some serious
programming.

Yeehaa!
Mark Sibly
