Hi Lazarus2000

> My questions to you learned and most helpful lot is, is chunky graphics any
> faster than planar when coding for AGA and an '030 without a graphics card?

I've heard that its not. But of course it depends on how much and what type of 
effects you are after. Doing c2p with an 030 will definately reduce your frame 
rate to 25fps max (maybe even max at a push, with a tailwind :). And a few 
people here have also said that Mildred doesn't work on their 030's, although 
some other people have said that it does.

> Would the use of Mildred allow me to retarget my game for a graphics card at a
> later stage?

It would allow you to retarget your game for a graphics card right at the start 
;) You'd also need to provide some way of selecting graphics cards screenmodes, 
although thats simply putting up an ASL requester and passing an extra option 
to the ScreenTags command.

> And the last question, and the most important at the moment is having had to
> come out of BLITZ mode to use Mildred how can I find the coordinates of the
> mouse since MOUSEX and MOUSEY no longer work?

The easiest way is to have a window on your screen. You can then get intuition 
events using Event (so that it doesn't block your main loop). So your mouse co-
ordinates can be got by WMouseX and WMouseY. And before anyone bitches about 
windows being slow, you don't actually do the rendering to the window.

Not that I've tried this with Mildred, but from what I've read.


