Hi Tony

> The GTMX has four labels and I would like to be able to activate the
> required label with the keystrokes rather than clicking with the
> mouse.
> 
> How can I do that?

ev.l=WaitEvent
Select ev
  Case #IDCMP_VANILLAKEY
	Select Chr$(EventCode)
	  Case "A"
		GtSetAttr gtlist,id,#GTMX_Active,1
	  Case "B"
		GtSetAttr gtlist,id,#GTMX_Active,2
	  ; etc
	End Select
End Select

If you also want Amiga key to be pressed with the key, you'll have to check the 
Qualifier command - the key values it can return are in teh Blitz online help. 
Note, that I don't know if the Eventcode will still be just the key in this 
case or whether you will need to check for #IDCMP_RAWKEY messages. Also, it may 
not work as using RAmiga+<something> is normally used for menus (I suppose you 
could set up a menu to activate the gtmx, in which case the keyboard handling 
for those menu shortcuts would be done automatically) and LAmiga+<something> is 
normally used for system things.


