Hi Matthew

> Has anyone got any example code for locking/unlocking workbench pens so that
> they can not be altered by other programs such as MUI & NewIcons. Cheers.

No code, but have a look at the Autodocs for graphics.library/ObtainPen_.

Code would be something along the lines of:

WBToScreen 0
*scr.Screen = Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))
*cm.ColorMap = scr\ViewPort\ColorMap
pennum.l = 20    ; the pen number to lock, set to -1 if pen number
				 ; is not important

; the colour we want the pen set to. Values are 32bits per gun and are left
; justified, so $FFFFFFFF means full intensity, $80000000 means about half
; intensity, etc. In this case, it is a crappy purpley color.
penred.l = $FF000000
pengreen.l = $00000000
penblue.l = $FF000000

pennum=ObtainPen(*cm,pennum,penred,pengreen,penblue,#PEN_EXCLUSIVE)
if pennum<>-1
	; we have pen, do whatever you want with it
	ReleasePen(*cm, pennum)
end if


