@NODE "Mail_187" " Re: MUI ARexx "
From: Rick Hodger <rick@simpleftp.co.uk>
Date: 06-24-00 20:56:32
Subject: @{b}Re: MUI ARexx@{ub}


Figured out how this damn thing works....and I was right in that it was to
do with the "static" part of the structure.

It appears that MUI is expecting the .MUI_Command structure to be a single,
continuous block of memory (hence the last field being just NULL entries). 
Blitz appears to use a linked list no matter what, so I did this:

NEWTYPE .arexxcmd
  cmd.MUI_Command[1]
End NEWTYPE
Dim temp.arexxcmd(1)
temp(0)\cmd[0]\mc_Name=&msg_connect$,#MC_TEMPLATE_ID,#CONNECT,0
temp(0)\cmd[1]\mc_Name=0,0,0,0
MUISet #APP,#MUIA_Application_Commands,&temp(0)\cmd

And this works, when called the ARexx script returns instantly and a
#CONNECT event is inserted into the input stream (MUIEvent or
MUIWaitEvent).  Unfortunatly you cannot have user interaction this way (eg.
"connect ftp://localhost/"). To do user interaction you have to use
something like:

url$="URL/A"
temp(0)\cmd[0]\mc_Name=&msg_connect$,&url$,1,&connecthook

...and create a hook for the &connecthook address.  Unfortunatly, I just
realised that there is another command, which takes a single hook for it's
parameter, and that hook is used whenever MUI cannot map a command to one
it knows.  So all your arexx stuff can be done by creating a hook to handle
all the arexx stuff, and then use a command like:

MUISet #APP,#MUIA_Application_ARexxHook,&arexxhook

So know I'm just busy trying to write the hook for this thing :)

